THREE men that were seated in a VW Golf 7 were shot several times by unknown men. It's alleged that the shooting incident was taxi-related. Two of the men succumbed to their wounds, while another is recovering in hospital. Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said the men were seated in a white VW Golf 7 when they were approached by armed men who fired several shots at them while parked at a traffic intersection on the R102, near Duffs Road.  According to IOL, three firearms were recovered in the Golf, while the roadway was closed to traffic while teams investigated further. A graphic video of the three men in the white Golf 7 shortly surfaced on social media, showing the driver that had died, and the front passenger who was shot in the neck and head. While the third passenger could be seen outside the car laying on the ground bleeding. 